"title": "7160: servants of the Lord",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7160: servants of the lord",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A description of individuals, groups, and the nation of Israel. Isaiah portrays a unique servant whom the NT identifies as Jesus Christ.</p>\n<h2>Individuals as servants of the Lord</h2>\n<h3>The patriarchs as servants of the Lord</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod32:13\">EXO 32:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen18:3\">GEN 18:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen32:10\">GEN 32:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut9:27\">DEU 9:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr16:13\">1CH 16:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps105:6\">PSA 105:6</a></p>\n<h3>Moses as the servant of the Lord</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod14:31\">EXO 14:31</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num12:7-Num12:8\">NUM 12:7–12:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut34:5\">DEU 34:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh1:1-Josh1:2\">JOS 1:1–1:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh1:7-Neh1:8\">NEH 1:7–1:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal4:4\">MAL 4:4</a></p>\n<h3>Other leaders as servants of the Lord</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num14:24\">NUM 14:24</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh5:14\">JOS 5:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh24:29\">JOS 24:29</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg2:8\">JDG 2:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg15:18\">JDG 15:18</a></p>\n<h3>David as the servant of the Lord</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps89:20\">PSA 89:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam23:11\">1SA 23:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam7:5\">2SA 7:5</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr17:4\">1CH 17:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs14:8\">1KI 14:8</a></p>\n<h3>Other kings as servants of the Lord</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs3:7-1Kgs3:9\">1KI 3:7–3:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr32:16\">2CH 32:16</a></p>\n<h3>Individual prophets as servants of the Lord</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs14:18\">1KI 14:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs18:36\">1KI 18:36</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs14:25\">2KI 14:25</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa20:3\">ISA 20:3</a></p>\n<h3>Paul as the servant of the Lord</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts27:23\">ACT 27:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:1\">ROM 1:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph3:1\">EPH 3:1</a></p>\n<h3>Other individual believers as servants of the Lord</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam1:11\">1SA 1:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job1:8\">JOB 1:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job2:3\">JOB 2:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job42:7-Job42:8\">JOB 42:7–42:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hag2:23\">HAG 2:23</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:38\">LUK 1:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:48\">LUK 1:48</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:29\">LUK 2:29</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas1:1\">JAS 1:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet1:1\">2PE 1:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jude1:1\">JUD 1:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:1\">REV 1:1</a></p>\n<h3>Pagan kings as servants of the Lord</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer25:9\">JER 25:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa45:1\">ISA 45:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer43:10\">JER 43:10</a></p>\n<h2>Groups of servants of the Lord</h2>\n<h3>The people of Israel as the Lord's servants</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa41:8-Isa41:9\">ISA 41:8–41:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:42\">LEV 25:42</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:55\">LEV 25:55</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh1:6\">NEH 1:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh1:10\">NEH 1:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa43:10\">ISA 43:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer30:10-Jer30:11\">JER 30:10–30:11</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer46:27-Jer46:28\">JER 46:27–46:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:54\">LUK 1:54</a></p>\n<h3>Failure of the people of Israel to serve the Lord</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa42:19\">ISA 42:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg10:6\">JDG 10:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam12:10\">1SA 12:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:35\">NEH 9:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal3:14\">MAL 3:14</a></p>\n<h3>Priests as the Lord's servants</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod28:1\">EXO 28:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod28:41\">EXO 28:41</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev7:35\">LEV 7:35</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num18:7\">NUM 18:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb8:5\">HEB 8:5</a></p>\n<h3>Levites as the Lord's servants</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut18:7\">DEU 18:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr23:28-1Chr23:31\">1CH 23:28–23:31</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra6:18\">EZR 6:18</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek44:11\">EZK 44:11</a></p>\n<h3>Prophets as the Lord's servants</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer7:25\">JER 7:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer29:19\">JER 29:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer44:4\">JER 44:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek38:17\">EZK 38:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan9:6\">DAN 9:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos3:7\">AMO 3:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech1:6\">ZEC 1:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:34-Matt21:36\">MAT 21:34–21:36</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:2-Mark12:5\">MRK 12:2–12:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:10-Luke20:12\">LUK 20:10–20:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev10:7\">REV 10:7</a></p>\n<h3>Other nations as the Lord's servants</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps72:11\">PSA 72:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa56:6\">ISA 56:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zeph3:9\">ZEP 3:9</a></p>\n<h2>The Lord's servants recognised as such by pagans</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan3:26\">DAN 3:26</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan6:16\">DAN 6:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan6:20\">DAN 6:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:17\">ACT 16:17</a></p>\n<h2>The unique servant of the Lord</h2>\n<h3>Isaiah's vision of this servant</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa42:1-Isa42:4\">ISA 42:1–42:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa49:1-Isa49:6\">ISA 49:1–49:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa50:4-Isa50:9\">ISA 50:4–50:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa52:13-Isa53:12\">ISA 52:13–53:12</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's life identifies him as the Lord's servant</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:17-Matt12:21\">MAT 12:17–12:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:16-Matt8:17\">MAT 8:16–8:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:28\">MAT 20:28</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:45\">MRK 10:45</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:28\">MAT 26:28</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:24\">MRK 14:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:12-Matt27:14\">MAT 27:12–27:14</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:2-Mark15:5\">MRK 15:2–15:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:12\">MRK 9:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:29\">JHN 1:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:38\">JHN 12:38</a></p>\n<h3>NT leaders proclaim Jesus Christ as the Lord's servant</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:30-Acts8:35\">ACT 8:30–8:35</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts3:13\">ACT 3:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts3:26\">ACT 3:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom10:16\">ROM 10:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:21\">ROM 15:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:6-Phil2:8\">PHP 2:6–2:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:21-1Pet2:25\">1PE 2:21–2:25</a></p>\n<h2>The Lord's service</h2>\n<h3>An exclusive service</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut6:13\">DEU 6:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut10:12\">DEU 10:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut10:20\">DEU 10:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh22:5\">JOS 22:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh24:14-Josh24:24\">JOS 24:14–24:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:24\">MAT 6:24</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke16:13\">LUK 16:13</a></p>\n<h3>Serving the Lord as he requires</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:23-Col3:24\">COL 3:23–3:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps2:11\">PSA 2:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:74\">LUK 1:74</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:35-Luke12:36\">LUK 12:35–12:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom7:6\">ROM 7:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph6:7\">EPH 6:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim2:24\">2TI 2:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:16\">1PE 2:16</a></p>\n<h2>The Lord's care for his servants</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps35:27\">PSA 35:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa54:17\">ISA 54:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa65:13-Isa65:15\">ISA 65:13–65:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan3:28\">DAN 3:28</a></p>\n<h2>The reward of the Lord's servants</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev22:3-Rev22:5\">REV 22:3–22:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:37-Luke12:38\">LUK 12:37–12:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:17\">LUK 19:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:26\">JHN 12:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:14-John15:15\">JHN 15:14–15:15</a></p>",
